cs.IT, cs.OH, cs.NI, cs.PH, cs.COMM 

Reasoning: 
1. cs.IT (Information Theory): The paper presents an analytical model for assessing the performance of the bit-error-rate (BER) in differential m-level phase shift keying (m-PSK) transmission systems, which involves the analysis of information transmission and coding. 
2. cs.OH (Optimization and Control): The paper discusses the influence of equalization enhanced phase noise (EEPN) on the BER performance in optical transmission systems, which involves the optimization and control of the system parameters to minimize the impact of EEPN. 
3. cs.NI (Networking and Internet Architecture): The paper investigates the impact of EEPN on the signal-to-noise ratio (SNR) in different fiber dispersion, LO laser linewidths, symbol rates, and modulation formats, which are relevant to networking and internet architecture. 
4. cs.PH (Physics): The paper discusses the influence of EEPN on the BER performance in coherent optical transmission systems, which involves the analysis of physical phenomena such as phase noise and dispersion. 
5. cs.COMM (Communications and Networking): The paper presents an analytical model for assessing the performance of the BER in differential optical transmission systems, which is relevant to communications and networking.
